      "Menuitem": "ReceiveMode",
      "Description": "The Receive Modesetting determines howthe fax accessory receives fax jobs. Select one of the following options: ● Automatic ● TAM ● Fax/Tel ● Manual"
    },
    {
      "Menuitem": "Rings to Answer",
      "Description": "The Rings to Answer setting determines the number of times the phone rings before the call is answered by the fax accessory. NOTE: The default range for the available options for the Rings to Answer setting is location-specific. The range of possible Rings to Answer options is limited by location. If the fax accessory is not answering, and the Rings to Answer setting is 1, try increasing it to 2."
    },
    {
      "Menuitem": "Ring Volume",
      "Description": "The Ring Volume setting allows you to adjust the ringer volume."
    }
  ],
  "source": "docling"
}

Section: Menuitem / Description
Table data:
{
